OL,4,CTeachers' grades biased to more
OL,5,C'agreeable' pupils
OL,6, Teachers' grades could be biased
OL,7, towards students with more "agreeable"
OL,8, personalities - rather than actual
OL,9, ability, say psychologists.
OL,11,FA study found a 10% advantage in
OL,12,Fteachers' grades for those seen as
OL,13,Fhaving likeable personalities, compared
OL,14,Fwith results in anonymous exams.
OL,16,FUniversity researchers warned students
OL,17,Fshould not be "penalised" because of
OL,18,Fnegative expectations about them.
OL,20,FTeachers' grades will be used this year
OL,21,Ffor cancelled exams across the UK.
